			<h2>Getting into the Business</h2>
			<p>If you're a youngster interested in pursuing a career in the metal and steel industry, here are some steps to get started:</p>
			<ol>
				<li>Research: Learn about the different types of metals and steel, their properties, and applications.</li>
				<li>Education: Consider enrolling in vocational training or degree programs in fields like metallurgy, materials science, or mechanical engineering.</li>
				<li>Internship: Look for internship opportunities with metal and steel companies to gain hands-on experience.</li>
				<li>Networking: Attend industry events and join professional organizations to connect with professionals in the field.</li>
			</ol>
